In a large bowl, mix cream cheese, sugar, and 1 tablespoon milk with wire whisk until smooth. Gently stir in 1 1/2 cups whipped topping. Spread on bottom of crust. In a second bowl, stir pudding mix into remaining milk until well blended. (Mixture will be thick.) Immediately stir in remaining whipped topping. Spread over cream cheese layer. Refrigerate 4 hours.